<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABSOLUTELY WRETCHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Surely the designers of the fashions depicted in the Aug. 28 Style section 
("Absolutely Fabulous") were joking. Such plug-ugly outfits I've never seen 
before. 
</P>
<P>
 Rubber dresses yet. All that are missing are the fins and face masks. 
</P>
<P>
 The model isn't too swift either. Is that what is meant by the expression 
bee-stung lips ? 
</P>
<P>
 Where are you, Coco Chanel, now that we need you? 
</P>
<P>
 Eve Langstaff 
</P>
<P>
 Hemet  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Since fashion subscribes to the trickle-down theory, I wonder how these latest 
designer fantasies will manifest themselves in the mainstream, or if they will 
appear there at all. 
</P>
<P>
 Plastic, rubber, fishnet and stiletto heels seem better suited to the bedroom 
than the boardroom. Are these designers hinting that that's where women belong? 
</P>
<P>
 Brooke L. Thibault Garden Grove  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 That fashion display must be a rerun of something published in Streetwalkers 
Monthly. There is but one perfect four-letter word to describe these creations: 
UGLY. 
</P>
<P>
 Emanuel Morris 
</P>
<P>
 Torrance  
</P>
