<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE GRIT GOES ON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thanks for "The Man in the Iron Lung" (by Brenda Bell, July 31), but no thanks 
to letter-writer Leslie Bryant Morton or the other linguistically handicapped 
who want you to stop using good, strong words like crippled . As a physically 
helpless, pain-racked cripple with only her head and one hand still 
functioning, I protest the ministrations of the misguided language police. Fate 
has deprived me of my mobility, my teaching career and my social life, but I'll 
be darned if I'll let self-appointed disability experts deprive me of my grit. 
</P>
<P>
 Kathryn Lindskoog 
</P>
<P>
 Orange  
</P>
