<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEASON WITHOUT SONG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding the changes for the next television season: How far can this 
corporate paranoia go? Now, besides cutting the time between programs, we must 
do without the often delightful theme songs. Can you imagine such programs as 
"Cheers" or "All in the Family" without them? I can only envision a bleak 
season ahead. 
</P>
<P>
 Larry Ginsky, Glendale 
</P>
