<P>
EMMY OR NOT, IT'S 'MURDER' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the Sept. 11 issue of TV Times, an article about Emmy "losers" mentions 
Angela Lansbury and her lack of an Emmy.To us, she should have won every year. 
We've seen every episode (of "Murder, She Wrote) and watch it in reruns on USA. 
But I do believe Ms. Lansbury will not be too upset by being overlooked again. 
"Murder, She Wrote" is still in the Top 10 after 11 years and knocks off every 
feeble attempt at competition. 
</P>
