<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Gerald Levert, "Groove On," EastWest. While some of these grunting, 
groaning tracks are standard R&B, Levert throws a few curveballs.There's a 
surprisingly tender, David Foster-produced track, "I'd Give Anything," along 
with "How Many Times," a caressing plea to a potential lover stuck in an 
abusive relationship. At his best, the singer recalls the Philly-flavored brawn 
of his famous dad, O'Jay Eddie Levert. 
</P>
<P>
 Albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor) to four stars (excellent).  
