<TEXT>
<P>
 * * 1/2 Walter Becker, "11 Tracks of Whack," Giant. A dozen lost Steely Dan 
demos? The arrangements are sketchier than the Dan's and the lyrics are less 
obtuse -- though dealing with the same low-life characters -- but that's still 
the impression of this fairly casual-sounding set.If you've been waiting for 
some revelatory masterpiece the silent Dan partner has been keeping inside him 
all these years, you'll have to keep waiting. 
</P>
<P>
 Albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor) to four stars (excellent).  
</P>
