<P>
 * * 1/2 J.J. Cale, "Closer to You," Virgin. Endearing one minute and 
exasperating the next, Cale sometimes sounds as if he's just revving the engine 
during a tuneup.His 11th album in 22 years is typically living-room informal 
and intimate, but when he hits a blues-rock groove as deliciously earthy as the 
one in "Brown Dirt," the casual approach pays off. Albums are rated on a scale 
of one star (poor) to four stars (excellent).  
