</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CLEO LAINE 
</P>
<P>
 "Blue and Sentimental" 
</P>
<P>
 RCA  
</P>
<P>
 * * * 1/2 
</P>
<P>
 The Dankworths, Cleo and John, are both represented as songwriters here 
("Primrose Colour Blue," "A Cryin' Shame") along with two other brilliant 
Britains, Carroll Coates ("Afterglow" with Gerry Mulligan soloing, and "Love 
Comes and Goes" with George Shearing), plus Duncan Lamont's "Not You Again," 
also with Shearing.Joe Williams' guest shots on two tunes further strengthen 
this mainly low-key set (but it ends boisterously with Bessie Smith's "Soft 
Pedal Blues.") Cleo's sumptuous contralto does a splendid spot of overdubbing 
on the title tune. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor) to four (excellent).  
</P>
<P>
 Leonard Feather 
