 * * Ken Peplowski, "Live at the Ambassador," Concord Jazz. This conventional 
jam session has Peplowski on tenor and clarinet, but the high spots are Howard 
Alden's guitar solos.It's agreeable but less than essential listening. Sweets 
Edison pops in for three guest tracks. Main point of interest: the most cryptic 
song title of all time, Tal Farlow's "I Brung You Finjans for Your Zarf." 
