<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIRTY HANDS COULD BE FOOD POISONING CAUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An outbreak of E. coli poisoning traced to meat served at a festival may have 
been caused by a food service worker with dirty hands, a state official says. 
</P>
<P>
 Nine people who attended an Oktoberfest two weeks ago were poisoned by the 
deadly bacteria. Another 20 suspected cases are being investigated, health 
officials said Thursday. All the victims were recovering. 
</P>
