<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANADA MAY IMPOSE DRIVING BANS TO CRACK DOWN ON PROSTITUTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canada may impose driving bans on people convicted of buying sex with 
prostitutes in their cars, Justice Minister Allan Rock says. 
</P>
<P>
 The government wants a major crackdown on street prostitution with tougher 
curbs against both prostitutes and their clients, Rock told the Southam News. 
</P>
<P>
 Other measures being considered include increasing penalties for two-time 
offenders and mandatory prison sentences of at least five years for pimps 
living off the earnings of juvenile prostitutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
