<HEADLINE>
<P>
48 SEMIFINALISTS NAMED IN MERIT SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Forty-eight Westside high school seniors have been named semifinalists in the 
1995 National Merit Scholarship program. They will compete with about 15,000 
other semifinalists nationwide for the 6,700 scholarships scheduled to be 
awarded in the spring. 
</P>
<P>
 The semifinalists were selected based on their scores on the 1993 Preliminary 
SAT/National Merit Scholarship Qualifying Test. Finalists will be chosen in the 
spring and will be eligible for a wide range of scholarships, including 2,000 
National Merit Scholarships, which are worth $2,000 each. 
</P>
<P>
 The Westside semifinalists: 
</P>
<P>
 Beverly Hills High: Romina R. Aghai, Brian H. Cheung, Rona D. Ezer, Evelyn J. 
Kim, Maria S. King, Neil A. Lester, Allison B. Margolin, Jonathan D. 
