<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFTER 26 YEARS, MALIBU RECYCLING CENTER WILL CLOSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A drop-off recycling center on Civic Center Way will close Oct. 30 because 
there hasn't been enough material collected there to keep the site operating. 
</P>
<P>
 The center, operated by a company called Recycle America, was created in 1968 
and is believed to be one of the oldest recycling facilities in the nation. A 
citywide curbside recycling program went into effect in June, 1992, and a 
commercial recycling center opened this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092594-0143 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 082502 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
