<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND HOME SALES UP 20% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sales of new and existing homes in Southern California are up by 20% in the 
first eight months of this year compared to the same period last year, 
according to TRW REDI Property Data, a nationwide real estate information 
company. 
</P>
<P>
 Between January and August, more than 138,000 single-family homes and condos 
closed escrow in the six-county region, with an average selling price of 
$210,135. Sales were particularly strong in Orange and Riverside counties, 
which showed increases of 26.2% and 23.5%, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
