<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Disbud your camellias, leaving only one bloom bud per branch to get the 
largest blossoms.Leave some further down the stem for later bloom. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant Bearded Iris this month. 
</P>
<P>
 * Prune deadwood and weak or diseased branches of trees and shrubs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Pull out summer vegetable plants and annuals that are spent and add them to 
your compost pile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
