<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: CONSUMER REPORTS' RATES ATLASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Consumer Reports recently road tested six U.S. road atlases, rating Rand 
McNally the highest, based on accuracy, portability, completeness and ease of 
use. Next came AAA, Mobil, Gousha, American Map Corp. and Hammond, in that 
order. Some tips on road atlas buying: Look for the newest edition, and don't 
expect perfection -- all the atlases tested had some errors, alas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
