<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: ARKANSAS GETS A CASE OF THE BLUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The blues will blow into Helena, Ark., Oct. 7-8 for the ninth annual King 
Biscuit Blues Festival featuring Junior Kimbrough, Robert Jr.Lockwood, Pinetop 
Perkins and Sam Myers, among others. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 50,000 people are expected to pour into the Mississippi River town 
for the free festival which is named after a Helena institution, the "King 
Biscuit Time" blues radio show. 
</P>
<P>
 Performances will run from about noon to 11 p.m. both days. For more 
information contact Main Street Helena, P.O. Box 247, Helena, Ark. 72342; tel. 
(501) 338-9144. 
</P>
</TEXT>
