<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAPPY IN HUATULCO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regarding "The Next Cancun?" by Christopher Reynolds (Aug. 28): 
</P>
<P>
 In November, 1991, we flew to Huatulco, checked into the beautiful Sheraton 
resort and informed the concierge that we wanted to be married at their hotel. 
"Sorry senor, too much paperwork, not enough time," was the response, but we 
persisted. 
</P>
<P>
 With the enthusiastic help of the ladies at the Sheraton, the local judge (who 
spoke no English) and a sweet San Diego couple we met at the swim-up bar, we 
were treated to a beautiful wedding on the beach in front of the Sheraton! 
</P>
<P>
 We found the service great, the food what we hoped for, an enjoyable (and 
empty) golf course -- all in all a fabulous place for a marriage. We found none 
of the problems with our room that Mr. Reynolds mentioned; rather, every night 
the maids left flower petals across the bed, spelling felicidades . I have 
stayed at many Sheratons, but the service, people, and care we received in 
Huatulco was easily the best they could offer. 
</P>
<P>
 ELAINE & CHARLES PAPISH 
</P>
<P>
 San Dimas 
</P>
</TEXT>
