<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIORDAN RISKING LIVES BY NOT REPAIRING FIREHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Mayor Richard Riordan should resign! 
</P>
<P>
 It has been more than eight months since the earthquake, yet Fire Station No. 
70 (Reseda and Lassen) still hasn't been repaired, leaving Northridge 
residents' lives and property in constant peril. However, supermarkets and 
freeways were open days after the quake! The Santa Monica Freeway opened ahead 
of schedule, and even the Coliseum is in operation. 
</P>
<P>
 My sources told me that Riordan knows that faulty construction, triggered by 
the quake, caused the fire station to be shut down -- this facility was built 
under the Bradley Administration -- but that investigation was completed months 
ago. It is unconscionable that the city, due to the mayor's lack of leadership, 
has not made every effort to reopen the station long before now. 
</P>
<P>
 But what has Riordan accomplished since he was last sighted in Northridge at 
the photo op with President Clinton after the quake? 
</P>
<P>
 Riordan allegedly provided more police officers in the budget by "mirrors" -- 
coercing the Department of Water and Power to pay for them. Are those funds in 
the city's treasury yet? No. Independent departments shouldn't have to fund the 
city's bloated budget, except to reimburse it for direct services. Also, our 
"great negotiator" botched the salary negotiations with DWP employees and the 
police, causing a strike and a "blue flu" -- thereby endangering our citizens, 
instead of allowing the city's professional negotiating staff to do its job. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, Riordan has surrounded himself with an "elitist" staff that 
doesn't have the first clue how to administer one of the world's largest and 
important cities. 
</P>
<P>
 The mayor of Los Angeles should know that the only purpose for a charter 
municipality to exist is to provide safety -- police and fire services. Any 
other services are secondary! Therefore, due to his lack of leadership 
concerning Los Angeles' -- and especially Northridge's -- requirement that 
public safety be the No. 1 priority, Mayor Riordan should resign immediately. 
Councilman Hal Bernson, who should know better, shouldn't even consider running 
for reelection, for the same reason. 
</P>
<P>
 STEVEN A. MORGAN 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge 
</P>
