<P>
 Garden Grove 28, Sonora 24 -- Ruben Reyna rushed for 123 yards and two 
touchdowns, including the game-winner, in a nonleague game.  
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove's first victory of the season offset a strong performance by 
Sonora's Mark Gonzalez.The 6-4 senior tight end caught nine passes for 171 
yards, including a 65-yard touchdown that gave the Raiders (1-2) a 14-7 
first-quarter lead. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the third of six lead changes. 
</P>
<P>
