struck for his first score, darting 49 yards down the sideline. The Argonauts 
(1-2) moved ahead with 34 seconds remaining in the half, when Troy Haller 
completed his second touchdown pass to Brian Jones, this for two yards. 
Earlier, they hooked up on Garden Grove's first score, a 63-yard pass. Jones 
caught four of Haller's seven completions for 86 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora drove 46 yards on a last-gasp drive, but the Raiders could not convert 
on a fourth-and-5 play from the Garden Grove 30 with 1:15 left. AHMED ORTIZ 
