<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA POSTS ANOTHER SHUTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAUREN PETERSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ivan McCrae and John Patton combined for 136 yards rushing to propel Ventura 
College to its third consecutive victory in a 31-0 rout of L.A. Southwest 
College on Saturday night at Ventura High. 
</P>
<P>
 The shutout was the second in three games for Ventura this season and improved 
the resurgent Pirates to 2-0 in Western State Conference play. The victory 
marked the first time since 1990 that Ventura has won three games in a row. The 
Pirates were 0-10 last season. 
</P>
<P>
 McCrae (81 yards and a touchdown in 13 carries) and Patton (55 yards in seven 
carries) sparked a balanced offense guided by quarterback Aaron Triana (seven 
of 13 for 122 yards and one touchdown.) Triana threw one interception. 
</P>
