<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAFFEY STOPS ANTELOPE VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE YEAMAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Zach Brennan threw touchdown passes of 12 yards to Lucas Thompson and eight 
yards to Bryce Erickson to lead host Chaffey College to a 19-6 victory over 
Antelope Valley in a Foothill Conference opener Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Marauder quarterback Michael Gleich was sacked six times for 20 yards and 
completed 10 of 20 passes for 160 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Marauders (0-3) were held to 25 rushing yards in 36 carries, and top back 
Roosevelt Miller carried 16 times for 18 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley scored when Gleich hooked up with wide receiver Jason Craft on 
a 34-yard play in the third quarter. Troy Searcy's 60-yard kickoff return to 
the Chaffey 36 set up the touchdown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
