<HEADLINE>
<P>
VILLAGE CHRISTIAN BOWS TO MOJAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK CARULLI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chuck Pierce and Tim Molloy hooked up on two touchdown passes to fuel Mojave 
High's 12-9 victory over Village Christian in a nonleague game Saturday at 
Kennedy High. 
</P>
<P>
 Mojave scored the game-winning touchdown with 58 seconds remaining on a 
15-yard play, capping a 14-play, 75-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Village Christian kicker Ignacio Brache's 65-yard field-goal attempt fell 
short as time expired. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crusaders (1-2) led, 9-0, in the first quarter on Cory Reisner's 31-yard 
pass to Tim Gustafson and Brache's 35-yard field goal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
