<HEADLINE>
<P>
OAK PARK DOMINATES L.A. BAPTIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN BOLT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eric Ruhle and Ron Allen connected on scoring passes of 36 and 25 yards, and 
Ryan Johnson rushed for 184 yards and a touchdown, to fuel Oak Park High's 28-3 
victory over L.A. Baptist in a nonleague game at Alemany High on Saturday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park (3-0) dominated on both sides of the ball, outgaining the Knights, 
390-84. L.A. Baptist fell to 0-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Adrian Kaali-Nagy kicked a 35-yard field goal with two seconds left to avoid 
the shutout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
