<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONTCLAIR PREP'S ANDERSON EXPECTS TO MISS NEXT GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAIGE A. LEECH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montclair Prep running back Akil Anderson, who incurred a knee injury during 
Friday night's 7-0 victory over Kern Valley, said he will undergo a magnetic 
resonance imaging test Tuesday and expects to miss Friday's game against 
Kilpatrick. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson and Darrell Dent were injured in the first half and did not return. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson, a 6-foot, 185-pound junior who gained 73 yards in 10 carries, was 
hurt on the first play of the second quarter and had to be helped off the 
field. 
</P>
<P>
 "I planted my left foot to cut right and got hit with a helmet on the inside 
of my (left) knee," said Anderson, who rushed for five touchdowns against 
Horizon of San Diego a week earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Dent, a receiver/safety and one of the top baseball prospects in the area, 
suffered a concussion minutes after Anderson's injury. PAIGE A. LEECH 
</P>
</TEXT>
