<HEADLINE>
<P>
ST. GENEVIEVE FINDS PISANO IN LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES CHESNUTT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Vince Pisano, starting his first varsity game for St. Genevieve, 
showed he was ready for the A team, but couldn't keep the Valiants from a 24-12 
loss to Western Christian Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Pisano, up from the junior varsity with Randy Iaccino out because of a broken 
ankle, completed 19 of 32 passes for 207 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Rickey Estrada scored on two short runs but the Valiants (0-3) finished with 
minus-five yards rushing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
