<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; HOLLAND, FOSTER LEAD O.C. RUNNERS AT INVITATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the Golden West Invitational, Irvine Valley's Larry Holland finished 12th 
(20:56) and Fullerton's Rafaele Spennato finished 21st (21:32) in the four-mile 
men's race at Huntington Beach's Central Park. El Camino's Humberto Sanchez 
broke the course record by 16 seconds in 20:19. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton was fourth and Irvine Valley finished fifth in the team competition. 
The men's competition was won by Mt. San Antonio. Golden West finished eighth 
and Saddleback finished 10th. 
</P>
<P>
 In the women's race, Golden West's Kim Foster finished third (19:19) and 
Fullerton's Teresa Vargas finished fourth (19:33) behind El Camino's Sawako 
Nakamura, who broke the 5K course record by 26 seconds in 18:38. Irvine 
Valley's Mayra Medina (19:36) and Darlene Pruitt (19:36) finished sixth and 
seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Valley finished second behind El Camino. Golden West, Saddleback and 
Fullerton finished seventh through ninth. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Cuyamaca Invitational: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast College ran to improve today while running against top-quality 
athletes on the men's side. Coast's men placed second (45) in the invitational 
behind Cuyamaca (39), last year's State champion. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates were led on the men's side by David Bolton (22:58) who finished 
sixth overall, behind Cuyamaca's first-place finisher, Alisro Heredia (21:57), 
on the four-mile course. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Cypress water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 13, Mt. San Antonio 4 -- Dave Johnson scored four goals, Mustafa 
Hassan added two and Robbie Walsh recorded 12 saves to lead Cypress (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the San Diego Mesa water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 8, El Camino 7 -- Brian Pearce and K.C. Nance each scored four 
goals and Craig Gabert recorded seven saves to lead Saddleback (3-7) in the 
consolation round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
