<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAL LUTHERAN WINS ON 5 GOALS BY GALLEGOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jill Gallegos tied Rachel Wackerman's school record of five goals Saturday, 
leading Cal Lutheran to an 8-0 SCIAC victory over Whittier. 
</P>
<P>
 Freshman goalie Kim Carver had an easy afternoon in the net for Cal Lutheran 
(6-1, 4-0), saving the only shot her teammates allowed. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Holeman, Laura Heifner and Emily Kanney also scored for the Regals, who 
bombarded Poet goalie Helen Baron with 45 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Gallegos, who is second on Cal Lutheran's all-time scoring list with 49 goals, 
has 18 this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
