<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIDAY NIGHT FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bell Gardens 49, Lincoln 0--David York rushed for three touchdown to lead the 
Lancers to a nonconference rout of the Tigers at Bell Gardens. 
</P>
<P>
 York put Bell Gardens ahead 7-0 with a two-yard run to cap a 10-play, 60-yard 
scoring drive on Bell Gardens' first possession and start a game-long pattern 
for the Lancers.York scored on a 24-yard run on the Lancers' next possession to 
make it 14-0 at the end of the first quarter. Bell Gardens kept the rout going 
with 21 second-quarter points on runs by Adam Solorzano and York and a 51-yard 
interception return by Rolando Terrazas. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell Gardens kept its starters in through the third quarter, scoring twice 
more. Quarterback Eddie Negrete completed 11 of 18 passes for 169 yards, 
including a 28-yard scoring pass to Tadeo Gonzales. David Villegas capped the 
scoring with a 13-yard run.  
</P>
<P>
 Lincoln gained only 82 total yards against Bell Gardens' well-drilled defense. 
</P>
<P>
 Next week: Lincoln at Eagle Rock; Bell Gardens at Chino. TONY JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
