<P>
 Thousand Oaks 28, Franklin 21--Sophomore running back Oscar Canela scored on a 
four-yard run with 8:28 left to bring the visiting Panthers to within seven of 
Thousand Oaks, but the Lancers' one-two running punch of Brandon Jackson and 
Mike Thomas was too much. 
</P>
<P>
 Down 21-7 in the third quarter, Jeff Deno scored on a one-yard quarterback 
sneak for Franklin and then threw a six-yard scoring pass to senior wide 
receiver Johnnie Sanders, who had seven catches for 128 yards. Deno went 
17-for-34 for 197 yards. 
