<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIDAY NIGHT FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roosevelt 24, Jordan 13--The Roughriders dominated the second half of a 
Central League game at Jordan in handing the Bulldogs their 29th consecutive 
loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Jordan scored on a 43-yard pass from Termel Goss to Mitch Friend to open a 
13-10 lead with 9:12 in the third quarter, but Roosevelt outgained the Bulldogs 
after that, 143 yards to five. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior running back John Pineda scored two touchdowns in the last eight 
minutes for Roosevelt, on runs of three and 15 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Jordan, winless since 1991, had two spectacular touchdown plays nullified by 
penalties. A 72-yard pass from Goss to Friend in the second quarter and a 
91-yard run by Kevin Harris in the third were called back. Goss completed eight 
of 15 passes for 161 yards and two touchdowns, with one interception. 
</P>
<P>
 Next week: Locke at Roosevelt; Bell at Jordan. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
