<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: WATTS; FREE TALK TO FOCUS ON PRENATAL CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Watts Health Foundation will offer a free prenatal presentation Thursday 
at the Watts Health Center, 10300 S. Compton Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is one of the programs offered during the foundation's Latino 
Awareness Month. Presentations on how to maintain a healthy pregnancy will be 
given in Spanish and English. 
</P>
<P>
 On Friday, the foundation will present an exhibit by Huntington Beach artist 
Richard Perez from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the United Health Plan, 4200 E. Compton 
Blvd. The event will include a cultural awareness presentation by Eddie Farias, 
an outreach coordinator at the Northeast Community Clinic in Pasadena. A 
Mexican folk dance troupe from Veracruz will perform at 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (310) 671-3465, Ext. 373. 
