<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: LINCOLN HEIGHTS; GOODWILL SPECIAL SALE TO BE AT 2 
LOCATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Goodwill Industries of Southern California has scheduled its annual Preferred 
Merchandise Sale next month to benefit people with physical, mental and social 
disadvantages. 
</P>
<P>
 Every year, donations including antiques, furs, china, collectibles, Oriental 
rugs, crystal, jewelry, paintings and designer clothing are held back from the 
26 thrift stores throughout Los Angeles for the special sale, which will be 
Saturday and Oct. 2, 15 and 16. 
</P>
<P>
 The sale is from 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday and 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Oct. 2 at the 
main plant, 342 San Fernando Road. 
</P>
<P>
 It continues from 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. Oct. 15, and 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Oct. 16 at 
the Valley plant, 14565 Lanark, Panorama City. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 223-1211. 
