<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EAST LOS ANGELES; WORKSHOP TARGETS WOMEN IN BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California American Woman's Economic Development Corp. has scheduled the 
first in a series of entrepreneurial workshops designed to address the needs of 
women business owners. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop, "Breaking Through the Entrepreneurial Ceiling," will be from 
6:30 to 8:30 p.m. Wednesday at the East Los Angeles Community Union, 5400 E. 
Olympic Blvd. Other workshops will be monthly. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will evaluate business management styles and determine the 
efficiency of building a business. The cost is $15. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is required: Kathy Fleming at (310) 983-3747. 
</P>
