COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: HUNTINGTON PARK; 1,000 EXPECTED AT COLLEGE WORKSHOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Huntington Park High will host the second annual parent-and-student College 
Conference on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshops will provide college information to parents and students from 
Bell, Bell Gardens, Fremont, Garfield, Huntington Park, Jordan and South Gate. 
More than 1,000 students from grades 10, 11 and 12 are expected. Last year's 
conference drew more than 500 students and parents. 
</P>
<P>
 The conference is scheduled from 8 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. at the school, 6020 Miles 
Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (916) 445-8188. 
