<HEADLINE>
<P>
CUBA SEEKS TO DETER ESCAPE FROM CAMPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cuban authorities Saturday urged people not to attempt the dangerous return to 
Cuba from the U.S. Naval Base at Guantanamo Bay where thousands of Cuban boat 
people are being held. 
</P>
<P>
 The Interior Ministry said 59 people had escaped from the camps in the last 
three weeks, most over minefields separating the base from Cuban territory. 
Others had left by swimming. 
</P>
<P>
 The ministry urged Cubans to be patient, noting that one person had been 
killed and another seriously injured by mines. 
</P>
