<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO-CAR COLLISION IN IRVINE INJURES 6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Six people were injured when two cars collided at an Irvine intersection 
Friday night, sending one vehicle careening into a light pole and rolling onto 
its roof, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Officer Gregg Gibbs said a Honda driven by Collin Eckert, 20, of Irvine 
was traveling north on Yale Avenue with three passengers about 10:40 p.m. when 
it struck a Mazda going west on Bryan Avenue and driven by Mina Maghami, 40, 
also of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Eckert was arrested on suspicion of drunk driving and released from custody 
for treatment at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, Gibbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident is still under investigation, and it is not clear whether alcohol 
was a factor in the accident, Gibbs said.  
</P>
<P>
 The injured were taken to two area hospitals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
