THOUSANDS OF MESSAGES LOST IN PACBELL OUTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pacific Bell's Message Center malfunctioned for the second time in a little 
more than a month Friday, losing thousands of customers' messages. 
</P>
<P>
 PacBell officials were still trying to determine the cause of Friday evening's 
outage, which affected customers in area codes 415, 510, 408 and 707. Since its 
debut in 1991, the Message Center has been plagued by problems, generally due 
to call overloads or computer problems. 
</P>
<P>
 The Message Center has about 400,000 customers statewide. Many customers were 
without service for more than four hours Friday, PacBell spokeswoman Judy 
Peterson said. 
