<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WESTLAKE; POLICE OPEN OFFICE AT GOOD SAMARITAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Office space donated by the Hospital of the Good Samaritan has become the 
Rampart Division's newest police drop-in center. 
</P>
<P>
 Located in the hospital's adjacent Weingart Guest House, 1254 W. 6th St., this 
is the division's third such center.Two more are in the planning stages, Capt. 
Nick Salicos said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers will fill out reports at the center and take care of administrative 
tasks outside of division headquarters. Foot and bicycle patrols will also 
conduct business in the center. Local residents will have access to the 
facility for Neighborhood Watch meetings and other community-based policing 
activities. 
</P>
<P>
 The hospital also donated telephone lines with voice mail and some office 
furniture. Additional supplies are being donated by the community. 
</P>
<P>
 The 35-unit guest house is primarily used to house the families of patients. 
The new drop-in center is on the second floor, in an unused area, said Paul 
Kells, vice president of facilities for Good Samaritan. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers will have access to the center around the clock, but there is no 
permanent staff. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 847-3214. 
</P>
