<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: BIRTCHER MEDICAL LOSES $20.9 MILLION IN FISCAL YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Birtcher Medical Systems Inc., an Irvine surgical products manufacturer, 
posted a loss of $20.9 million, or $2.28 a share, for its fiscal year ended 
June 30.Most of the loss was recorded for the third quarter as a result of a 
divestiture and restructuring program. That compared to a loss of $2 million, 
or 22 cents a share, for the previous fiscal year.  
</P>
<P>
 Sales fell 18% to $34.3 million from $42 million. For the fourth quarter, the 
company lost $1.8 million, or 19 cents a common share, compared to a loss of 
$2.2 million, or 24 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier. 
Three-month sales were $7.3 million, down from $9 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
