<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dense-Pac Microsystems Inc.: The Garden Grove manufacturer of memory 
subsystems reported a loss of $359,227, or 2 cents a share, for its latest 
fiscal quarter.That contrasted with a profit of $241,410, or 2 cents a share, 
for the same period a year earlier. Sales for the company's second quarter, 
which ended Aug. 31, declined 10% to $2.8 million from $3.1 million. For its 
first half, the company said it lost $928,460, or 6 cents a share, contrasted 
with profit of $558,668, or 4 cents a share, for the corresponding six months 
of the previous year. Six-month sales were down 5% to $5.5 million from $5.8 
million. 
