<TEXT>
<P>
 Luther Medical Products Inc.: The Tustin catheter company said it lost 
$961,923, or 34 cents a share, for its fiscal year ended June 30, which 
included a loss on the disposal of business of $182,671.That contrasted with a 
profit of $44,510, or 2 cents a share, for the previous fiscal year. Revenue 
declined 18% to $2.3 million from $2.8 million. For its fourth quarter, the 
company reported a loss of $396,361, or 13 cents a share, compared to a loss of 
$19,908, or 1 cent a share, for the same period a year earlier. Three-month 
revenue rose 11% to $672,322 from $607,914. 
